abstract: President Donald Trump said Tuesday he knows the identity of the author known as “Anonymous,” the senior administration official who wrote an inside-the-White House account that painted the president as inept and dangerous.
snippet: President Donald Trump said Tuesday he knows the identity of the author known as “Anonymous,” the senior administration official who wrote an inside-the-White House account that painted the president as inept and dangerous.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Donald Trump said Tuesday he knows the identity of the author known as “Anonymous,” the senior administration official who wrote an inside-the-White House account that painted the president as inept and dangerous.
headline_main: Trump Says He Knows Identity of 'Anonymous' Tell-All Writer
headline_print_headline: Trump Says He Knows Identity of 'Anonymous' Tell-All Writer

abstract: The president will stay in Las Vegas this week as Democratic candidates debate down the Strip. His namesake hotel is abuzz with Secret Service agents, supporters and the simply curious.
snippet: The president will stay in Las Vegas this week as Democratic candidates debate down the Strip. His namesake hotel is abuzz with Secret Service agents, supporters and the simply curious.
lead_paragraph: LAS VEGAS — When Elaine and Robert Jacobs of Mansfield, Ohio, checked in for their three-night time-share vacation on Monday, the receptionist told them to expect tight security.

abstract: Nelson Mandela’s trial nearly 60 years ago was not filmed, but the words spoken still echo loudly.
snippet: Nelson Mandela’s trial nearly 60 years ago was not filmed, but the words spoken still echo loudly.
lead_paragraph: The trial for sabotage and a conspiracy to violently overthrow the government of South Africa that earned Nelson Mandela a life sentence in 1964 was not filmed. But its audio component was recorded; 256 hours of it, according to this film. “The State Against Mandela and the Others,” a documentary about that trial and its aftermath directed by Nicolas Champeaux and Gilles Porte, has clever, effective means of compensating for the absence of visual documentation. One is animation.
